I"S<p><strong>Gay Pride float in Twin Falls Western Days parade can’t be too gay.</strong> The Southern Idaho Gay Lesbian Bisexual and Transgender Community Center has to call itself the Community Center, nix rainbows, no AIDS education pamphlets. Parade chairwoman Lisa Cuellar: “No rainbows, no gay pride, not anything like that.” Wells Fargo can still have their little “Conestoga Wagon”, though. And the churches can have their thick, hairy crosses and happy faces. Hopkins in the <a href="http://www.magicvalley.com/articles/2008/05/29/news/top_story/137679.txt">Times-News</a>.</p>
